 Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Of Germanic origin (via French  <b>Adélaïde</b> ), from <i>adal</i> ‘noble’ + <i>heid</i> ‘kind, sort’. It was borne in the 10th century by the wife of the Holy Roman Emperor Otto the Great. She became regent after his death and was revered as a saint. The given name increased in popularity in England during the 19th century, when it was borne by the wife of King William IV; she was the daughter of the ruler of the German duchy of Saxe-Meiningen. The Australian city of Adelaide was named in her honour."],"variants":[]},{"name":"of","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Oswald   or any of the various other names beginning with <i>Os-</i>."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Adelaide of Diessen-Andechs was born in 1082 as the daughter of Adolf von Eppan and Irmgard N. She married Albrecht I Count of Tyrol in 1117. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1163, at the age of 81."},"et":{"1082–1163":"1082–1163","1075–1125":"1075–1125","–1140":"–1140","1101–1165":"1101–1165","1123–1180":"1123–1180","1065–1116":"1065–1116","–Female":"Surnud","AFT 1116":"pärast 1116","1165":"1165","1065":"1065","1163":"1163","1075":"1075","Abt 1125":"umbes 1125","1140":"1140","1082":"1082","1180":"1180","1117":"1117","1116":"1116","1125":"1125","1123":"1123","1101":"1101","about 1101":"umbes 1101","Bolzano, Trentino-South Tyrol, Italy":"Bolzano, Trentino-Alto Adige, Itaalia","Trento, Trento, Trentino-Alto Adige, Italy":"Trento, Trento, Trentino-Alto Adige, Itaalia"},"fi":{"1082–1163":"1082–1163","1075–1125":"1075–1125","–1140":"–1140","1101–1165":"1101–1165","1123–1180":"1123–1180","1065–1116":"1065–1116","–Female":"Kuollut","AFT 1116":"1116 jälkeen","1165":"1165","1065":"1065","1163":"1163","1075":"1075","Abt 1125":"noin 1125","1140":"1140","1082":"1082","1180":"1180","1117":"1117","1116":"1116","1125":"1125","1123":"1123","